init_text: Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. 50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn that no one else went into isolation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: One day, you arrive at work to find a strange-looking letter in your mailbox.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The letter isn't signed, but you can tell immediately that it's from the Etoile Noire.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You open up the package, and inside is a letter in French.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You can't understand the message, but you remember your French well enough to realize that this is the same broadcast that's included in the package

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Do you wait until an official reply arrives from the Government of the United States?
